    <long-description>The Nieuport 12 (or Nieuport XII) was a French sesquiplane reconnaissance, fighter and trainer aircraft 
    used by France, Russia, Great Britain and the United States during World War I. Later production examples were built as trainers.
    Manufactured 1915-1918 and served widely until the late 1920s.It is fitted with Clerget, 130 hp (97 kW) Clerget 9B engine.
    It could be also fitted with either a 100 hp (75 kW) Clerget or 110 hp (82 kW) Le Rhone 9 engines. This model is based on Emmanuel BARANGER's Nieuport-11.
    </long-description>
